[
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.1",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Be ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;",
    "hash": "3d24e3cd69b9cd5ab6dc1379969a3e5def73a7884502ccc84eb35d1ea66b118a"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.2",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us, and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweetsmelling savour.",
    "hash": "0767974710fb75d0c3669851bd554085eb1c1170bcc4b326a4e8d86e94f7b746"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.3",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "But fornication, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not be once named among you, as becometh saints;",
    "hash": "9d45d56f340f538f27c0c9b7f44749135ed42f8cf9a579dfe701ac8c9f5d5bb7"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.4",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks.",
    "hash": "82f2cf887b9d05e6983e096e6c5dcf857d45fa73d624d6f4447d41ec10df194a"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.5",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.",
    "hash": "8d3256ced7f576c6867245e12c51f99e373eab9a13a466ed224815baacb20618"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.6",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience. {disobedience: or, unbelief}",
    "hash": "29e227a32b6b0f8a9b44f1394acfc4e6ab57f958be614200f03a63c9bee53a84"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.7",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Be not ye therefore partakers with them.",
    "hash": "7c594e0c43350a1de68389ed1a804aa16ae78ad731297260fa48fee579570f33"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.8",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For ye were sometimes darkness, but now {are ye} light in the Lord: walk as children of light:",
    "hash": "e23598a1e2b1ab94355a551afd9c73b0111bcc1fa15afa3f263c1d8e65e50508"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.9",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "(For the fruit of the Spirit {is} in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)",
    "hash": "a8b2cdb6f30a9b627f5e983d0b7a14217f3f42ad99a7862862c40d6c645f5b91"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.10",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Proving what is acceptable unto the Lord.",
    "hash": "57f9ff8fd58d2984f294d3b55dbb6a6ae9243579766b117c811e53cb3dd89050"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.11",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove {them}.",
    "hash": "90ee13e2e872daa9e7e8860967b34d6b7f2964ddec283da7084d89e9bb80e1b0"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.12",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.",
    "hash": "c555a3253afaec23aeb97d17a39e90c3f4591319c58a131ff6fe08cf899661b5"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.13",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light: for whatsoever doth make manifest is light. {reproved: or, discovered}",
    "hash": "63702b21b7e68fd542b38f3a726321fc385d3fd344b4ffcd2348d5775af7d73f"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.14",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give thee light. {he: or, it}",
    "hash": "246b65750b04fa4df327efdad2eb71301a4284355380c626947018de11f4f5c1"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.15",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,",
    "hash": "bb9bf7b839b78152e786b346bca9b5a0cc5d8208f533fa492dfba29e320f1499"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.16",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Redeeming the time, because the days are evil.",
    "hash": "2c19dccd5bae72bef4302b986624f168f812bc1a395b7d22b6ed7416c73b612a"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.17",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Wherefore be ye not unwise, but understanding what the will of the Lord {is}.",
    "hash": "baa0487dec9a08c6c2026a3784429b1c714e87a87637b9a3559c99e3839531a9"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.18",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;",
    "hash": "1030028d6640bcba21bdd9ab90a6c853e96bc066261b5dbd4e55dc5eae922c77"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.19",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;",
    "hash": "3a66415ee284841e3272c4d054854ee37f6b403d595597d82ab2d814b72a85e1"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.20",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;",
    "hash": "d01be1200e1a5cb8c1defdeb2d441da38975ac5a893f1bb231aa31e50baf7691"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.21",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God.",
    "hash": "b42fa9065ee088ee9628603b29abf89352738b94234a31e77f0628ceb2995363"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.22",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.",
    "hash": "08b15d8232f49fb49c4b6b66ce7c0a2809a2beb2b9ca065ea20bef0f519f1b23"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.23",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body.",
    "hash": "0385b047635c1c5801a1702960639af7868ba438864d0371062088d6220e5914"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.24",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so {let} the wives {be} to their own husbands in every thing.",
    "hash": "f5cb0a9b40721ff919a4ee7ee37f3c1b36f81bd8cac3be6691e5e0da198561da"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.25",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for it;",
    "hash": "78e71891ecba6875135e30e2a079a74313e7fc83fc32806c5caeda4dc1f67798"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.26",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,",
    "hash": "626e0e5d7dc649a77bbf9459647106f15871de95ed7c009a5d04312af7d76649"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.27",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish.",
    "hash": "4071adbd4d094b354173a130bcaaf20d4cd6d472f3b86b06524f7b603c992802"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.28",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "So ought men to love their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself.",
    "hash": "e4d06071d8e11d15f180c0972e709cd43dcda67b95a911ea62e9cb59c85658cb"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.29",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For no man ever yet hated his own flesh; but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church:",
    "hash": "79b26be4d44bd2920d56dbbe41a653ad3c79e7b08814e55030011be646140822"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.30",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "For we are members of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones.",
    "hash": "1433673da49bc98820c85227b069ca63d2ae5b043eca8a4223f56427d2dfeecf"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.31",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.",
    "hash": "bf1f6a1d10c5f9fb7004d4865d8a0750e3967d6282565bf129a958520791b5c7"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.32",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.",
    "hash": "ac7cd1c1f13eafdb9e5cb24b1e572fe6f93f9761a1b850fa976cb7c45bc192ed"
  },
  {
    "id": "EPH.5.33",
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "bookNum": 49,
    "bookAbbrev": "EPH",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Nevertheless let every one of you in particular so love his wife even as himself; and the wife {see} that she reverence {her} husband.",
    "hash": "30a5879f5f56b2a4db303925ee68e66dcdf40e1e07f87a5f35911717b0669acc"
  }
]